---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const phase1 = [
  { day: "Day 1",  topic: "What Is Data, Databases, and SQL?",              status: "Completed", link: "/day-1" },
  { day: "Day 2",  topic: "SELECT : Reading Data From Tables",              status: "Completed", link: "/day-2" },
  { day: "Day 3",  topic: "WHERE : Filtering Your Data",                    status: "Completed", link: "/day-3" },
  { day: "Day 4",  topic: "String Functions, Date Functions, and CASE",     status: "Completed", link: "/day-4" },
  { day: "Day 5",  topic: "Aggregate Functions : COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, MAX", status: "Completed", link: "/day-5" },
  { day: "Day 6",  topic: "Subqueries and Nested Queries",                  status: "Completed", link: "/day-6" },
  { day: "Day 7",  topic: "JOINs Part 1 : INNER JOIN and LEFT JOIN",        status: "Completed", link: "/day-7" },
  { day: "Day 8",  topic: "JOINs Part 2 : RIGHT, FULL, SELF, CROSS JOIN",   status: "Completed", link: "/day-8" },
  { day: "Day 9",  topic: "UNION, INTERSECT, EXCEPT",                       status: "Completed", link: "/day-9" },
  { day: "Day 10", topic: "Window Functions : ROW_NUMBER, RANK, LAG, LEAD", status: "Completed", link: "/day-10" },
];

const phase2 = [
  { day: "Day 11", topic: "CTEs : Common Table Expressions",                status: "Completed", link: "/day-11" },
  { day: "Day 12", topic: "Recursive CTEs : Hierarchies and Sequences",     status: "Completed", link: "/day-12" },
  { day: "Day 13", topic: "NULL Handling : COALESCE, NULLIF, IFNULL",       status: "Completed", link: "/day-13" },
  { day: "Day 14", topic: "Advanced Window Functions : NTILE, FIRST_VALUE, PERCENT_RANK", status: "Completed", link: "/day-14" },
  { day: "Day 15", topic: "Writing Data : INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, UPSERT",  status: "Completed", link: "/day-15" },
  { day: "Day 16", topic: "Table Design : Data Types, Keys, Constraints",   status: "Completed", link: "/day-16" },
  { day: "Day 17", topic: "Indexes : What They Are and When to Use Them",   status: "Completed", link: "/day-17" },
  { day: "Day 18", topic: "EXPLAIN and Query Optimization",                 status: "Completed", link: "/day-18" },
  { day: "Day 19", topic: "Advanced Patterns : Pivoting, Gaps and Islands", status: "Completed", link: "/day-19" },
  { day: "Day 20", topic: "Full Review : 20-Query Challenge",               status: "Completed", link: "/day-20" },
];

const phase3 = [
  { day: "Day 21", topic: "LeetCode Easy Blitz : Clear the Backlog",        status: "Completed", link: "/day-21" },
  { day: "Day 22", topic: "LeetCode Medium : DE Interview Problems",        status: "Completed", link: "/day-22" },
  { day: "Day 23", topic: "LeetCode Medium + First Hard Problem",           status: "Completed", link: "/day-23" },
  { day: "Day 24", topic: "Real DE Query Patterns",                         status: "Completed", link: "/day-24" },
  { day: "Day 25", topic: "SQL Dialects : Snowflake, BigQuery, PostgreSQL", status: "Completed", link: "/day-25" },
  { day: "Day 26", topic: "DE Patterns : Deduplication, Slowly Changing Dims", status: "Completed", link: "/day-26" },
  { day: "Day 27", topic: "Production SQL : dbt, Pipelines, Daily Queries", status: "Completed", link: "/day-27" },
  { day: "Day 28", topic: "Mock Interview : Real Interview Questions",       status: "Completed", link: "/day-28" },
  { day: "Day 29", topic: "Gap Review : Shore Up Weak Areas",               status: "Completed", link: "/day-29" },
  { day: "Day 30", topic: "Final Mock : 90 Minutes, 10 Questions, No Notes",status: "Completed", link: "/day-30" },
];

const supplement = [
  { day: "Day 31", topic: "Snowflake & BigQuery Deep Dive",                 status: "Completed", link: "/day-31" },
  { day: "Day 32", topic: "dbt Fundamentals and SQL Transformations",       status: "Completed", link: "/day-32" },
  { day: "Day 33", topic: "System Design for Data Engineers",               status: "Completed", link: "/day-33" },
  { day: "Day 34", topic: "Portfolio Project : End-to-End SQL Pipeline",    status: "Completed", link: "/day-34" },
  { day: "Day 35", topic: "Final Review and Next Steps",                    status: "Completed", link: "/day-35" },
];
---

<Base>
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-12 px-4 prose prose-lg">
    <h1 class="text-center">35-Day SQL Mastery Plan</h1>
    <p>
      This is my structured roadmap from absolute SQL zero to Data Engineer ready, covering
      fundamentals, JOINs, window functions, CTEs, query optimization, and real-world DE patterns.
      I'll update statuses and links as I go.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>📘 Phase 1 (Days 1–10): SQL Foundations (Absolute Beginner to Intermediate)</li>
      <li>⚙️ Phase 2 (Days 11–20): Advanced SQL + Performance</li>
      <li>🏋️ Phase 3 (Days 21–30): LeetCode Grind + Real DE Queries</li>
      <li>🚀 Supplement (Days 31–35): DE Tools, dbt, and Portfolio Project</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Phase 1 -->
    <h2 class="mt-10">📘 Phase 1: SQL Foundations (Days 1–10)</h2>
    <p>Goal: Go from zero to writing JOINs, subqueries, aggregations, and window functions confidently. LeetCode Easy problems mapped to each day.</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
      <table class="min-w-full text-sm divide-y divide-gray-200">
        <thead class="bg-gray-50">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Day</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Topic</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Status</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Post</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
          {phase1.map(item => (
            <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">{item.day}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{item.topic}</td>
              <td class={`px-4 py-2 font-semibold ${item.status === 'Completed' ? 'text-green-600' : item.status === 'In Progress' ? 'text-blue-600' : 'text-yellow-600'}`}>{item.status}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">
                {item.link ? (
                  <a href={item.link} class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">View Post</a>
                ) : (
                  <span class="text-gray-400">Coming Soon</span>
                )}
              </td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 2 -->
    <h2 class="mt-10">⚙️ Phase 2: Advanced SQL + Performance (Days 11–20)</h2>
    <p>Goal: Master CTEs, recursive queries, NULL handling, indexes, EXPLAIN, and advanced analytical patterns used in real Data Engineering work.</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
      <table class="min-w-full text-sm divide-y divide-gray-200">
        <thead class="bg-gray-50">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Day</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Topic</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Status</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Post</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
          {phase2.map(item => (
            <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">{item.day}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{item.topic}</td>
              <td class={`px-4 py-2 font-semibold ${item.status === 'Completed' ? 'text-green-600' : item.status === 'In Progress' ? 'text-blue-600' : 'text-yellow-600'}`}>{item.status}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">
                {item.link ? (
                  <a href={item.link} class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">View Post</a>
                ) : (
                  <span class="text-gray-400">Coming Soon</span>
                )}
              </td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 3 -->
    <h2 class="mt-10">🏋️ Phase 3: LeetCode Grind + Real DE Queries (Days 21–30)</h2>
    <p>Goal: Crush LeetCode SQL Easy and Medium problems, practice real Data Engineering query patterns, and simulate actual interviews.</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
      <table class="min-w-full text-sm divide-y divide-gray-200">
        <thead class="bg-gray-50">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Day</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Topic</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Status</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Post</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
          {phase3.map(item => (
            <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">{item.day}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{item.topic}</td>
              <td class={`px-4 py-2 font-semibold ${item.status === 'Completed' ? 'text-green-600' : item.status === 'In Progress' ? 'text-blue-600' : 'text-yellow-600'}`}>{item.status}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">
                {item.link ? (
                  <a href={item.link} class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">View Post</a>
                ) : (
                  <span class="text-gray-400">Coming Soon</span>
                )}
              </td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <!-- Supplement -->
    <h2 class="mt-10">🚀 Supplement: DE Tools + Portfolio (Days 31–35)</h2>
    <p>Goal: Go beyond SQL. Learn Snowflake, BigQuery, dbt, system design for data, and build a portfolio project that ties everything together.</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-4">
      <table class="min-w-full text-sm divide-y divide-gray-200">
        <thead class="bg-gray-50">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Day</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Topic</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Status</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-2">Post</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
          {supplement.map(item => (
            <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-2 font-medium">{item.day}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">{item.topic}</td>
              <td class={`px-4 py-2 font-semibold ${item.status === 'Completed' ? 'text-green-600' : item.status === 'In Progress' ? 'text-blue-600' : 'text-yellow-600'}`}>{item.status}</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-2">
                {item.link ? (
                  <a href={item.link} class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">View Post</a>
                ) : (
                  <span class="text-gray-400">Coming Soon</span>
                )}
              </td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-10">📝 How I'm Tracking Progress</h2>
    <p>
      Each day I write a blog post covering the day's concepts, key queries, and LeetCode problems solved.
      Status updates from <strong>Upcoming</strong> → <strong>In Progress</strong> → <strong>Completed</strong> as I go.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>🟡 <strong>Upcoming</strong>: not started yet</li>
      <li>🔵 <strong>In Progress</strong>: currently working on this</li>
      <li>✅ <strong>Completed</strong>: post published, problems solved</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      LeetCode problems are mapped to each day's topic. Easy first, then Medium as the days progress,
      with Hard problems introduced in Phase 3.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>